		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Gene Zeiger</strong></span>&rsquo;s first poem, written in fifth grade, contained the immortal lines &ldquo;For you are full of so much charm, / that to you will come no harm. / Not even from a tiger, / for you are the daughter of Mr. Zeiger.&rdquo; She lives in Shelburne, Massachusetts.</p><a href="/contributors/genie-zeiger" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

							</footer>
						</article>


